You should read up on [Flexbox](https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/). It will make your life easier: 
In flexbox it would be like 

    .main-container: {
       display: flex;
       flex-direction: column;
     }

Instead of using float:left, you can use: &quot;display:inline-block&quot;, this will put the div next to each other. I&#39;ll also recommend you to put some padding on each side of the divs.

You can see your working code here, this is the most cleanest way I found:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .nextto{
      display: inline-block;
      width: 30%;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div style=&quot;width:100%&quot;&gt;
     &lt;div class=&quot;nextto&quot;&gt;Test&lt;/div&gt;
     &lt;div class=&quot;nextto&quot;&gt;This is a longer test. This is a longer test. This is a longer test.&lt;/div&gt;
     &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Try to use flexboxes
```
 &lt;div style=&quot;display: flex; flex-direction: row; justify-content: space-between&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;Test&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;This is a longer test. This is a longer test. This is a longer test.&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
```
Inside child divs you can set width or flex-basis

