answers.body_markdown:
The code uses short variable declaration, but no new variables are declared because the [blank identifier](https://golang.org/ref/spec#Blank_identifier) `_` does not represent a variable name.

Use the following code:

    for _, _ = range x {
        //Do some work
    }

Note use of [assignment](https://golang.org/ref/spec#Assignments) instead of [short variable declaration](https://golang.org/ref/spec#Short_variable_declarations).

Better yet, don&#39;t assign any variables as shown in comment by mh-cbon:

    for range {
       //Do some work
    }

The variable-free form was added in [Go 1.4](https://golang.org/doc/go1.4#forrange).

When none of the variables are being used, you can ignore the blank identifiers.

    x := [5]float64{1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
    for range x {
        //Do some work
    }

As noted by @MonteDude , the `_` variable is already defined. This is why you get a `no new variables on left side of :=` error.

