**In this specific example**, you can&#39;t render the child without rendering the parent.

But, it surely can be achieved with higher composition using [Context API][1].


```
//   v Container with Context provider
&lt;Container&gt;
  &lt;Parent&gt;
//     v Can be rendered without Parent&#39;s rendering
    &lt;Child /&gt;
  &lt;/Parent&gt;
&lt;/Container&gt;

//  v In your case, can&#39;t be achieved.
&lt;Parent&gt;
//  v Must be aware of props change,
//    therefore, the parent must be rendered.
  &lt;Child /&gt;
&lt;/Parent&gt;
```


  [1]: https://reactjs.org/docs/context.html

